article.headline: Oral Roberts 90, S. Dakota St. 82
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Warren Niles scored 25 points and made all five 3-point attempts as Oral Roberts shot 65 percent from the field and defeated South Dakota State 90-82 on Saturday night. The Golden Eagles (6-12, 3-3 Summit League) connected on 14 of 17 3-pointers, but the Jackrabbits (11-5, 3-2) kept pace, making 13 of their 29 attempts. Nate Wolters kept South Dakota State in the game with his hot shooting, making 12 of 16 shots, and he finished with a game-high 32 points. Wolters made 4 of 5 3-point attempts. Oral Roberts, which led 42-36 at halftime, made 34 of 52 shots and outrebounded South Dakota State 35-22. South Dakota State got as close as 78-76 with 2:38 remaining, but two Niles 3-pointers gave Oral Roberts an 84-78 lead, and the Golden Eagles continued to stretch their lead over the final minute.
